# 5. 廊下の語らい

An: “And autumpne stirreth it most of al, oft it hath bin said.”
An: Um, so... Everyone says that things are most charming in fall...
An: “Forsooth it may be so, yit nought can enflame the herte as can...”
An: That may be true, but nothing is as moving as...
Mizuki: Ooh, look at you, An! You've come so far since yesterday.
An: I guess. Well... I do have to check the textbook for vocabulary and conjugations, but I'm getting there.
An: I looked at my vocab list in the bath last night, but it was stressful since I couldn't really memorize much.
Mizuki: Really?
Mizuki: Well then! I have an exciting present for such a hardworking student!
An: Huh?
Mizuki: Here you go!
An: It's...a notebook?
Mizuki: Yup! I made it last night. I put together a whole bunch of study notes like important words to learn and conjugation crib sheets.
An: Wow... You went to all this trouble for me?
Toya: This is...impressive. Your notes are very clear and concise.
Mizuki: They are, aren't they?! Feel free to keep praising me!
Akito: Yeah, you really took it seriously. What brought that on so suddenly?
Mizuki: Um, rude. I just want An not to get held back a year.
Mizuki: An, I'm rooting for you to make it into second year armed with this!
An: Thank you, Mizuki! I'll make good use of it!
Akito: Yes! I solved it!
Toya: Good work, Akito.
Rui: Everyone, how about we stop for a while? Breaks are important for maintaining concentration.
Tsukasa: Yes! I've been getting thirsty, so I'll go grab a drink.
Mizuki: How about rock paper scissors then? Loser buys for everyone.
An: Ooh, I like that! Let's do it!
Toya: That's fine by me... However, it will be a lot for one person, so how about the last two people go?
Mizuki: Okay!
Akito: Here we go.
Mizuki: Rock...paper...
An: Scissors!
An: *Sigh* I can't believe I lost...
An: Not to mention how they all asked for snacks and other food on top of drinks, so the bags are stuffed to the brim.
Rui: Hehe, I suppose they're just that tired. I could take your bag?
An: Oh, that's fine, Kamishiro! You already took the heavier bag.
An: Actually, are you fine carrying that?
Rui: It's no trouble. I wouldn't want to tire you out since you need to save your energy for your studies.
An: Hahaha, you're exaggerating.
An: But... Thank you, really.
An: Not just for carrying the bag... For teaching us, too. You explain things so clearly, and it's all so helpful.
Rui: There's no need to thank me. I've been having fun myself with things being so lively.
An: Really? That's good to hear!
Rui: Also... Mizuki seems to be having fun. I certainly wasn't expecting that notebook.
An: Yeah, I was surprised too! That was such a thoughtful gesture.
An: And yesterday, when I said thank you for helping us with studying, Mizuki just said, “Don't mention it!” and “It was fun.”
Rui: I see.
Rui: I'm glad.
An: Oh, that reminds me... Didn't the two of you go to the same junior high school?
An: Were you close back then too?
Rui: I'd say so... We'd meet up and chat from time to time.
Rui: But, Mizuki...
Rui: Mizuki seems to be having much more fun now.
Rui: These study sessions are proof of that.
An: Really? I guess I only know the Mizuki we have right now.
Rui: Hehe. I think it comes down to having friends who are good influences.
Rui: And I believe you're one such friend, Shiraishi.
An: Me?
Rui: I think having friends like you is a big help for Mizuki.
An: Friends like me...?
An: Hmm... But I really haven't done anything.
An: I mean, I just enjoy spending time with Mizuki, so I wanted to be friends!
An: So, I don't feel like I've done anything to help. Oh, but...
An: If Mizuki is glad that we became friends, I couldn't be happier!
Rui: I see.
An: We're back! And we bring drinks and snacks!
Mizuki: About time, guys! I'm starving here.
An: Sorry! But we got the French fries you asked for.
Mizuki: Ooh! At long last!
Akito: Got my cheesecake?
An: Yes sirree. Is this the right one?
Akito: Yeah, thanks.
Rui: Thanks for waiting, Tsukasa, Toya. Shiraishi has the food, and the drinks are in my bag.
Tsukasa: Got it! Many thanks, Rui, Shiraishi!
Tsukasa: Let's see, this coffee is yours, right Toya? It's hot, so be careful.
Toya: Thank you, Tsukasa.
Rui: Here's your orange juice, Shiraishi.
Rui: Be sure to eat plenty and get ready to study more.
An: Okay!
